Hey guys,

I've written a custom asset class which takes care of loading textures async'ly using loaders and asset manager. I've also written a custom drawable class which takes this asset as a parameter. I'm initializing an Image with this drawable. However, when the texture gets loaded, the image doesn't draw. Here is the code snippet from the custom drawable class that I've written:

protected CoreAsset asset;

...

/\* 
- returns true if asset is loaded
- and populates the region by calling
- setRegion() when the asset loads
- for the first time 
  */

protected boolean checkAsset() {
...
}

...

@Override
    public void draw(Batch batch, float x, float y, float width, float height) {
        if (checkAsset()) {
            super.draw(batch, x, y, width, height);
        }
    }

JsonReader from last nigtly (25.04.2014) fails to read escaped double quptes in strings like:
{
text: "test with \"some quotes\""
}

A month ago (mid of March) the same code was working OK. Seems like last changes of JsonReaded broke something.

