{
    text: "test with \"some quotes\""
}

A month ago (mid of March) the same code was working OK. Seems like last changes of JsonReaded broke something.

Here sample:

```
    public static void main(String[] arg)
    {
        new LwjglApplication(new ApplicationAdapter()
        {
            @Override
            public void create()
            {
                super.create();

                String multilineString = "One\ntwo\nthree";

                JsonValue objectJson = new JsonValue(JsonValue.ValueType.object);

                JsonValue strangeStringJson = new JsonValue(JsonValue.ValueType.stringValue);
                strangeStringJson.name = "count";
                strangeStringJson.set(multilineString);
                objectJson.child = strangeStringJson;
                objectJson.size++;

                JsonValue.PrettyPrintSettings prettyPrintSettings = new JsonValue.PrettyPrintSettings();
                prettyPrintSettings.outputType = JsonWriter.OutputType.json;

                String result = objectJson.prettyPrint(prettyPrintSettings);

                Gdx.app.log("JSON", result);

            }
        }, new LwjglApplicationConfiguration());
    }
```

Will output:

```
JSON: {
"count": "One
two
three"
}
```

and that is invalid JSON. As I understand the correct way to escape newlines is by using \n.

Problem seems to be located in
https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/blob/master/gdx/src/com/badlogic/gdx/utils/JsonWriter.java

OutputType.quoteValue function (and maybe quoteName).
